Sentencas: A newly developed interconnect alloy for solid oxide fuel cells, containing Fe, Cr, Mn and Mo as well as other minor elements and designated as FeCM, is investigated on its poisoning effect on (La0.8Sr0.2)(0.95)MnO3-delta (LSM) cathode by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy and microstructure observation.
Titulo: Improved chromium-poisoning on lanthanum strontium manganite cathode in presence of a newly developed iron-chromium based interconnect alloy for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with commercial SUS430 stainless steel, which is usually used as a essential interconnect in the SOFCs stacks, the FeCM alloy as the interconnect reduces the ohmic of the cell (R-Omega) and polarization resistance of the cathode (R-p) and increases the electrochemical performance of the cathode.
Titulo: Improved chromium-poisoning on lanthanum strontium manganite cathode in presence of a newly developed iron-chromium based interconnect alloy for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 850 degrees C the R-Omega remains almost unchanged at a level slightly above 2.0 Omega cm(2) and the R-p decreases from 5.76 to 1.68 Omega cm(2) within 20 h, while the cathode potential at 200 mA min(-1) is virtually stabilized at below 1.0 V and the overpotential is decreased from 0.43 to 0.16 V.
Titulo: Improved chromium-poisoning on lanthanum strontium manganite cathode in presence of a newly developed iron-chromium based interconnect alloy for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Based on the evidence of a narrower oxide deposition zone on the electrolyte surface near the cathode and a deposition-free cathode/electrolyte interface, this improvement is attributed to the reduced degree of volatilization of oxide scale formed on the surface of the FeCM alloy.
Titulo: Improved chromium-poisoning on lanthanum strontium manganite cathode in presence of a newly developed iron-chromium based interconnect alloy for solid oxide fuel cells
